3. PERSONAL DATA PROTECTION — LGPD PRINCIPLES

This software was developed in observance of the principles of the Brazilian General Data
Protection Law (LGPD — Law No. 13,709/2018) and, to the extent applicable, the General
Data Protection Regulation (GDPR — Regulation (EU) 2016/679).

3.1. No Collection or Transmission of Data to the Author

This software does not collect, transmit to the Author or to any third party under the
Author's control, share, or commercialize user data of any kind.

All data entered and managed by the user — including names, phone numbers, messages,
appointments, and custom variables — is stored exclusively on the user's local device.

3.2. Exclusively Manual Export and Import

The transfer of data between devices or for backup purposes is performed solely through
manual operations using the export and import features available within the software.

3.3. Responsibility for Processing Third-Party Data

As the controller of the data entered into the software, the user bears full and sole
responsibility for the processing of third-party personal data entered into the application.


4. USER RESPONSIBILITY

By installing and using this software, the user acknowledges and agrees that:

a) The user is the sole and exclusive party responsible for how the application is used;

b) The user is responsible for the legality of all communications sent through this software;

c) The user undertakes not to use this software to commit crimes or civil offenses;

d) The user agrees not to use this software contrary to the WhatsApp Acceptable Use Policy
   and WhatsApp Terms of Service.


5. USE RESTRICTIONS

This software does not offer, enable, or was designed to support:

a) Large-scale automated sending, spam, or non-personal communication;

b) Mass messaging;

c) Circumventing, bypassing, or violating controls or policies imposed by WhatsApp.


6. MODERATE USE AND RESPONSIBLE SCHEDULING

This software provides scheduling features designed for personal, professional, and moderate
use, with the following technical safeguards:

- One message per appointment: each appointment is linked to a single recipient;
- Random delay between sends: the scheduling service automatically applies a random interval;
- No mass dispatch: the application provides no mechanism for simultaneous bulk sending.


